               Distribution and Misc. Legal Nonsense


Please distribute all files intact and without modifications, unless the
author of those modifications indicates clearly the files affected.  There
are no warrenties, expressed or implied as to the suitability or usability
of the provided files.  The author does not accept liability for any
consequental damages.

Precognition is copyright 1991, 1992, 1993 by Lee Willis as intellectual
property. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.

No restrictions are placed by the Author on programs created using the
Precognition builder program and/or the Precognition library, source, or
headers.  (i.e. you can sell programs which make use of Precognition
and you don't have to pay me.)

Precognition is FreeWare, and other parties may not sell it for profit or
personal gain. Costs for distribution may, however, be recovered. If you
wish to add warrenties or services beyond those already provided, a fee may
be changed for services rendered (GNU style).  The author of the Precogniton
reserves the right to modify or amend the terms covering their contributed
works.  If you have questions about these terms, or any others here, please
contact the author.

